subject: p12074041
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest were obtained. A single-lead left-sided AICD is again seen with lead extending to the expected position of the right ventricle. There has been interval removal of a right internal jugular central venous catheter. There is minimal interstitial edema. No large pleural effusion or pneumothorax. The cardiac silhouette remains mildly enlarged. The aorta is tortuous. No focal consolidation seen.
Impression: Minimal interstitial edema and mild cardiomegaly.
